data.description: Back on the market after the buyers fell through.   Beautiful home in a quiet Copperton neighborhood. This home has been fully upgraded. It has amazing mountain views. It is a short walk to the city park. The previous owners installed a new HVAC system, tankless water heater, water softener and upgraded the electrical and plumbing. They also have a mini split AC unit to cool the attic. Inside features hardwood floors, crown molding, arched openings and coffered ceiling. Stainless appliances and upgraded cabinets and butcher block counters. The upstairs attic was converted into a bedroom. The basement has a living room and bedroom with carpet and future bathroom. Outside you will enjoy having a private and shared driveway to get to your garage and RV parking. You're only minutes from shopping and entertainment. We included a photo from the summer with the sellers permission.   Square footage figures are provided as a courtesy estimate only and were obtained from public records .  Buyer is advised to obtain an independent measurement. There is a 2nd laundry hookup in the attic closet.
